74
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:50,290
-You crazy jerk.
-You crazy bitch.

75
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:51,666
-Fuckface.
-Fucking twat.

76
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:52,583
Son of a bitch.

77
00:04:53,042 --> 00:04:56,170
It won't be easy to make a miniseries

78
00:04:56,754 --> 00:04:58,589
with new stories for each episode.

79
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:01,634
As you can see from the synopsis,

80
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:05,013
we already have enough stories
to make 16 episodes.

81
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:07,682
We also have some extra stories
for replacement in case they are not fun.

82
00:05:07,765 --> 00:05:10,518
If we get favorable reviews,
we can also consider

83
00:05:10,601 --> 00:05:12,312
making a sequel.

84
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:15,064
I believe that's the biggest advantage
of this drama.

85
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:18,276
A drama is supposed to make viewers
curious about the next episode.

86
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:20,528
It's not a 20-minute-long sitcom
that airs 5 days a week.

87
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:22,697
The viewers should wait five days
for the next episode.

88
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:27,118
But this is a drama where viewers can skip
one episode without being curious.

89
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:29,704
Aren't you worried about that?

90
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:33,374
The goal of our drama is somewhat similar,
but a little different.

91
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,335
It's not just about a bait,
but about empathy and sympathy.

92
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:38,171
And the power of characters.

93
00:05:38,254 --> 00:05:40,089
Do you think they have the power?

94
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:42,508
Don't you think it's too focused on women?

95
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:45,136
-Time slot.
-Female characters aren't strong enough.

96
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:47,013
The script that hasn't earned a time slot

97
00:05:47,096 --> 00:05:50,641
simply remains as letters
that almost got made into a drama.

98
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:53,144
The script of the aspiring screenwriter,
along with her dream,

99
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:56,022
ends up taking a long sleep

100
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,316
somewhere deep inside her external drive.

101
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:01,611
The only thing she can do
during her crisis

102
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:03,446
is to wait for the decision-makers.

103
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:07,533
To be more exact, the decision of
the elderly who don't like my writing.

104
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:09,368
All I can do is wait for them.

105
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:11,579
Making a drama isn't that easy.

106
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,928
You're staying still for too long.

107
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:29,764
-Yes, I'm on my diet.
-You call staying still a diet?

108
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:31,599
Yes, eating less and moving less
is more efficient

109
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:33,476
than eating a lot and moving a lot.

110
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,353
Shouldn't you eat less and move more--

111
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:38,064
Why do you even care?

112
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:41,526
-Are you all right?
-Yes.

113
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:44,028
Okay, you're far from all right.
Can I help with anything?

114
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:45,321
Give me like ten billion won.

115
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:47,448
Will that be enough to have you?

116
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:50,159
No, you can't have me with that money.

117
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,994
Why not?

118
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,121
If you had that money,

119
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:55,123
you would've given it to
a younger and hotter guy.

120
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:58,793
Just what do you want me to do?

121
00:06:58,876 --> 00:07:01,003
Give me ten billion won,
no strings attached, or forget it.

122
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:04,090
Okay. I'll get going. Jin-joo.

123
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,508
I love you ten billion.

124
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:07,468
-Just go.
-Okay.

125
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:21,524
To solve the situation,
I need to put in more effort.

126
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:23,860
The logical saying

127
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:27,196
that effort will not betray you
sometimes sounds too abstract.

128
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:30,199
It's natural to work hard.

129
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,909
But when it's hard to do
the natural thing,

130
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:34,245
I start thinking it may not be
a natural thing after all.

131
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:36,539
When I start to wonder
if someone who was born with it

132
00:07:36,622 --> 00:07:39,500
said such thing, pretending to
know it all,

133
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,836
I just stay still.

134
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:48,009
This may be my instinct telling me
to reserve the energy while I can.

135
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:52,388
Let's not eat.

136
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:54,515
"If a man will not work,
he shall not eat."

137
00:07:55,057 --> 00:07:57,059
This saying that sounds like
an unfair labor law

138
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,604
sometimes feels like
it's the standard labor law.

139
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,606
This life isn't worth living.

140
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:04,650
My soul is instinctively refusing

141
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:07,403
to live this life with fat.

142
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,572
I will not eat.

143
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,291
-Hello?
-Let's eat.

144
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:22,376
-Who is this?
-I'll come to you.

145
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:24,378
You got the wrong number.

146
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:25,880
Are there any good restaurants near you?

147
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:40,311
I'd have invited you out to a meal
if you had been starving yourself,

148
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:41,771
but I see that you've been eating well.

149
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:43,773
I haven't been eating, you punk.

150
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:48,361
Ta-da.

151
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,613
-Take it.
-What is this?

152
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:52,490
Green onions.

153
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:58,454
I mean, why are you giving it to me
as if this was a bouquet?

154
00:08:58,829 --> 00:09:00,540
There's no specific way
of giving green onions.

155
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,085
Will you keep me standing here?

156
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:18,766
We need to keep up our strength.

157
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,059
I know

158
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:23,104
you're already doing fine
but we're going to need more energy.

159
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:24,105
So let's eat green onions.

160
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,732
-Why green onions?
-It will energize you.

161
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:29,777
-I know you've had your breakfast.
-I haven't, you punk.

162
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:32,154
You should eat more even if you're full.
That's love for humanity.

163
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:36,033
Do you know it tastes great
to add green onions to tteokbokki?

164
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:38,953
-You hate tteokbokki?
-Yes.

165
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:42,248
Why are you telling me that now?
I've been cooking at yours.

166
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:44,333
You told me to eat green onions.
I'll eat that.

167
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:48,462
Right. You're right.
Let's eat green onions.

168
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,569
It's tasty.

169
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:14,905
The green onion stole the thunder.

170
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,376
This green onion is tasty.

171
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:30,755
Right? You may hate tteokbokki, but
you have to give the sauce some credit.

172
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:33,924
Gochujang is the best ingredient
for a sauce. I love that about Korea.

173
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:38,804
Eat up.

174
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:43,934
Why are you doing this to me?
You're being too nice.

175
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:48,606
My grandfather used to say

176
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:51,484
"If a man did not eat, he shall not work."

177
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:53,527
So you want me to work now?

178
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:56,113
Yes. Not working

179
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:57,823
makes me feel guilty.

180
00:10:57,948 --> 00:11:01,035
Let's eat up and work hard.

181
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:04,747
Don't feel guilty.

182
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:08,459
It may seem like we're doing nothing
on the outside,

183
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,545
but it's different on the inside.

184
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:16,425
Our organs are working hard
to digest the food we ate.

185
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:21,347
We are in the middle of doing
something absolutely sacred.

186
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:24,141
This kind of feels like simple labor.

187
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:27,478
A human body isn't so simple, is it?

188
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:30,272
No, it's not.

189
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:35,528
Stay still. Just stay still.

190
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:37,822
Okay.

191
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:41,075
By the way...

192
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:43,536
You know we should find
a production company, right?

193
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:44,870
