in episode 15 and 16.

512
00:33:56,284 --> 00:33:58,911
And we are allowed to shoot
inside the restaurant

513
00:33:58,995 --> 00:34:00,538
on a weekday afternoon for free.

514
00:34:01,497 --> 00:34:05,460
We'll be saving around
five to six million won a day.

515
00:34:05,543 --> 00:34:07,670
Pass it over to the marketing team.

516
00:34:07,754 --> 00:34:09,714
You should focus more on production.

517
00:34:09,964 --> 00:34:11,674
Writer Kim Gyeong-jin broke off
his agreement.

518
00:34:11,758 --> 00:34:14,010
Sorry? We worked so hard on it though.

519
00:34:14,093 --> 00:34:17,096
I don't get why writers are so nasty.

520
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:20,266
It's like they are competing to see
who's the nastiest of them all.

521
00:34:20,349 --> 00:34:22,685
Will they score points
to get a reward for being nasty or what?

522
00:34:23,978 --> 00:34:26,481
We've already received the investment.

523
00:34:26,814 --> 00:34:28,649
It's so hard to find a piece to work on.

524
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:30,943
Right.

525
00:34:31,152 --> 00:34:33,613
Also, big agencies
are being territorial these days.

526
00:34:34,739 --> 00:34:36,532
What about the rookie writer?

527
00:34:36,866 --> 00:34:38,367
The script is a mess.

528
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:42,747
She can't even write
but she has the pride of a master.

529
00:34:42,830 --> 00:34:45,541
Is that what they teach
at the writer training institute?

530
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,713
Once I handle the wet mop case,

531
00:34:51,214 --> 00:34:52,715
I'll start meeting with writers.

532
00:34:53,341 --> 00:34:55,676
I'll also check the works by newbies.

533
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:56,844
What about the wet mop?

534
00:34:57,970 --> 00:35:00,306
Oh, that damn jerk?

535
00:35:00,723 --> 00:35:02,433
That son of a bitch
always causes a problem.

536
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:18,241
Here are the documents.

537
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:21,619
Gosh, thank you.

538
00:35:23,871 --> 00:35:25,206
What did Ms. Lee say?

539
00:35:26,833 --> 00:35:28,417
I never heard her swear before.

540
00:35:28,501 --> 00:35:30,294
-To you?
-No.

541
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:35,758
As if the seam of your tight pants
suddenly ripped

542
00:35:35,842 --> 00:35:37,343
because they are too small for you,

543
00:35:37,844 --> 00:35:40,930
the stress was too much for her,
so she popped a seam and swore.

544
00:35:42,056 --> 00:35:44,433
Let's try our best not to do that.

545
00:35:45,268 --> 00:35:46,853
I think you'll be cute if you swear.

546
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:48,479
I'm good at swearing.

547
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:51,858
-Come on. Try it then.
-I'm really good.

548
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:53,776
No way. Try it.

549
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:57,697
Jae-hun, I didn't know
you could taunt like this.

550
00:35:58,489 --> 00:36:01,742
Swear if you can. I know you can't.

551
00:36:01,826 --> 00:36:04,203
I said I'm good at it, you son of a bitch.

552
00:36:06,789 --> 00:36:08,583
Right, you are good.

553
00:36:17,508 --> 00:36:19,677
-I like them.
-Shoes?

554
00:36:19,927 --> 00:36:21,137
What do you think?

555
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:25,183
-I like these better.
-Why?

556
00:36:26,350 --> 00:36:27,476
All right.

557
00:36:35,651 --> 00:36:37,445
Are you allowed to link arms with him?

558
00:36:38,112 --> 00:36:39,739
We have you and the cameraman.

559
00:36:39,822 --> 00:36:41,490
And even if we get caught,
he's just my manager.

560
00:36:41,991 --> 00:36:44,285
Do you always go out with Min-jun?

561
00:36:44,493 --> 00:36:45,953
We went to the same high school.

562
00:36:46,495 --> 00:36:48,664
Isn't it uncomfortable to work
with your friend?

563
00:36:48,789 --> 00:36:49,790
We're not close.

564
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:54,170
He's close to you as a manager
but not as a high school friend.

565
00:36:54,253 --> 00:36:55,671
I can't do anything without him.

566
00:36:56,547 --> 00:36:59,508
That's surprising. That sentence
itself is full of affection,

567
00:36:59,842 --> 00:37:01,385
but it didn't sound affectionate at all.

568
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:02,762
Because she has no affection.

569
00:37:05,389 --> 00:37:06,390
What?

570
00:37:07,892 --> 00:37:09,602
-Don't do that.
-Okay.

571
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:21,405
Does she really walk around so much
on her day off?

572
00:37:21,739 --> 00:37:23,699
That is 100 percent her natural self.

573
00:37:25,284 --> 00:37:28,079
That's why she never gains any weight.

574
00:37:28,537 --> 00:37:29,705
She doesn't eat either.

575
00:37:30,998 --> 00:37:32,500
We shouldn't have filmed a documentary.

576
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:35,086
We should've taken her
to a hospital to do a CT scan.

577
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,421
She's superhuman.

578
00:37:39,465 --> 00:37:40,549
Seriously.

579
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:48,849
-Kill this for me.
-Get down here.

580
00:38:13,416 --> 00:38:16,085
They kind of make a cute couple.

581
00:38:34,603 --> 00:38:36,230
Intellectual nourishment.

582
00:38:38,190 --> 00:38:39,317
Do you like reading books?

583
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,027
No, I like buying books.

584
00:38:42,028 --> 00:38:43,654
-I'm glad to hear that.
-Why?

585
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:47,366
It's time we need physical nourishment
more than intellectual nourishment now.

586
00:38:47,450 --> 00:38:48,659
Don't you read a lot?

587
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:50,786
I do. After I eat.

588
00:38:52,204 --> 00:38:54,123
Are you aware we walked
more than 20,000 steps today?

589
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:57,084
Hey, you got a call from the agency.

590
00:38:57,168 --> 00:38:58,294
He's asking if you can drop by.

591
00:38:58,544 --> 00:38:59,962
-What?
-He has a script for you.

592
00:39:00,546 --> 00:39:01,380
Really?

593
00:39:08,763 --> 00:39:10,473
Lee So-min the woman and actress.

594
00:39:10,556 --> 00:39:13,100
She's a woman and an actress,
but she may not be human.

595
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:14,852
How can she say "Let's go party"

596
00:39:14,935 --> 00:39:16,771
when she walked for 20,000 steps
without eating?

597
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:20,107
But the thing is...

598
00:39:20,524 --> 00:39:23,569
She's so energetic in her free time,

599
00:39:23,652 --> 00:39:26,572
but why does she always lack energy
on camera as an actress?

600
00:39:27,823 --> 00:39:29,742
-Because she doesn't want to work?
-No.

601
00:39:29,825 --> 00:39:32,953
When she's on camera
and is unaware of how she looks,

602
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:34,246
the psychological pressure

603
00:39:34,330 --> 00:39:36,374
must be dragging her down
like heavy sandbags.

604
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:38,626
Cameras are like sandbags?

605
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:42,546
Actors and actresses must have
incredible energy after all.

606
00:39:46,133 --> 00:39:49,303
Even I feel exhausted
to be on camera right now.

607
00:39:53,974 --> 00:39:56,727
This isn't a TV show,
so you can be yourself.

608
00:39:57,353 --> 00:39:59,188
So you want me to talk about So-min?

609
00:39:59,271 --> 00:40:01,107
Yes. Say a few words.

610
00:40:01,690 --> 00:40:02,775
You can say it now.

611
00:40:04,276 --> 00:40:06,320
You're so pretty, So-min.

612
00:40:10,741 --> 00:40:13,411
Is that it? Anything else?

613
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:16,789
You're so pretty, So-min.

614
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:20,709
Well, anything else?

615
00:40:22,128 --> 00:40:23,546
You're so cute, So-min.

616
00:40:24,255 --> 00:40:25,548
You're not a robot.

617
00:40:25,631 --> 00:40:28,551
Just say whatever you wanted to say.

618
00:40:29,301 --> 00:40:31,053
You're so cute, So-min.

619
00:40:40,521 --> 00:40:41,480
A weekend drama?

620
00:40:41,647 --> 00:40:43,399
The director came to us

621
00:40:43,482 --> 00:40:45,192
to ask if you're available.

622
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:47,486
First a web drama,
and now a weekend drama?

623
00:40:48,362 --> 00:40:51,240
I don't want a weekend drama.
I want a weekday drama.

624
00:40:51,323 --> 00:40:53,576
Two episodes will be aired on Saturday.

625
00:40:53,659 --> 00:40:56,036
Not just on Saturday. I want weekdays.

626
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:58,205
It's a Saturday-Saturday drama.

627
00:40:58,747 --> 00:41:01,292
This sounds better than a weekday drama.

628
00:41:01,375 --> 00:41:03,461
It's like a lottery. You'll hit a jackpot
if you get lucky.

629
00:41:03,586 --> 00:41:04,962
What are the odds of winning a lottery?

630
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:06,547
It depends on the game.

631
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:09,216
The higher the losing chances are,
the higher the dividend rate is.

632
00:41:10,676 --> 00:41:12,720
So you're betting me on a team
with high losing chances

633
00:41:12,803 --> 00:41:13,762
to hit a jackpot.

634
00:41:13,846 --> 00:41:15,055
We're betting on a team

635
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:17,183
with a high dividend rate for your honor.

636
00:41:17,349 --> 00:41:21,270
And this writer has been hitting
over ten percent ratings on weekends.

637
00:41:21,437 --> 00:41:22,730
Just have a look at the script.

638
00:41:23,606 --> 00:41:24,899
I'm only reading the first episode.

639
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:26,609
It gets fun from the second episode.

640
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:31,780
Let's talk, Min-jun.

641
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,827
You're so pretty, So-min.

642
00:41:38,287 --> 00:41:39,455
Aren't you going to follow her?

643
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:41,665
I'm not shooting.

644
00:41:41,832 --> 00:41:43,751
No matter what she does,

645
00:41:43,834 --> 00:41:45,669
I will not stop in the middle of a meal.

646
00:41:45,836 --> 00:41:47,296
That's a new rule.

647
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:53,511
You can stop working with So-min now.

648
00:41:54,553 --> 00:41:56,430
-Sorry?
-I know it's hard.

649
00:41:56,555 --> 00:41:58,432
No, it's not. I'm fine.

650
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:00,518
You've been working for so long now.

651
00:42:00,601 --> 00:42:02,686
You can do better than her road agent.

652
00:42:03,562 --> 00:42:05,189
Well, you're the boss.

653
00:42:05,272 --> 00:42:06,815
Go to Haenaem ENT.

654
00:42:07,358 --> 00:42:08,567
You'll be a team manager.

655
00:42:08,651 --> 00:42:10,486
Why? Are you firing me now?

656
00:42:10,611 --> 00:42:13,489
What? I don't want you to leave.

657
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:16,367
But we already have
four team managers at this agency.

658
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:18,619
You have enough experience
but I can't give you a title here.

659
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:20,829
Haenaem is a big agency,

660
00:42:21,163 --> 00:42:23,207
and the CEO keeps things clean.

661
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,000
But this is too sudden.

662
00:42:25,084 --> 00:42:27,253
I don't want you to go either.

663
00:42:30,464 --> 00:42:31,549
What?

664
00:42:32,091 --> 00:42:33,968
Why do you look sad all of a sudden?

665
00:42:34,051 --> 00:42:35,719
They've been thinking hard

666
00:42:35,803 --> 00:42:37,763
because they have no one with experience.

667
00:42:38,472 --> 00:42:39,848
They asked me to send you over.

668
00:42:40,474 --> 00:42:43,143
This is a great chance.
Do your best there.

669
00:42:43,352 --> 00:42:44,478
I never said I'll go.

670
00:42:44,562 --> 00:42:46,355
I know you're a loyal one.

671
00:42:47,189 --> 00:42:49,191
I know you care about me.

672
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:50,859
It's fine.

673
00:42:52,319 --> 00:42:53,571
What are you saying?

674
00:42:55,447 --> 00:42:57,241
What? Why are you crying?

675
00:42:57,658 --> 00:42:59,743
I'm not crying, you punk.

676
00:42:59,994 --> 00:43:01,662
Why do you keep acting these days?

677
00:43:02,705 --> 00:43:03,872
You're actually good, you know.

678
00:43:04,790 --> 00:43:06,208
Gosh.

679
00:43:36,655 --> 00:43:38,282
It's so weird.

680
00:43:39,408 --> 00:43:43,203
My ex-girlfriend
as my senior's girlfriend.

681
00:43:43,954 --> 00:43:44,997
That's not right.

682
00:43:45,080 --> 00:43:47,166
Are you shooting a drama?
Why are you talking to yourself?

683
00:43:49,251 --> 00:43:50,461
When did you get here?

684
00:43:51,378 --> 00:43:52,713
We're in an elevator.

685
00:43:53,589 --> 00:43:55,507
Did your ex-girlfriend become
your senior's girlfriend?

686
00:43:55,758 --> 00:43:58,052
No. It's about a drama script.

687
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:00,429
You're too old for a messy relationship.

688
00:44:00,596 --> 00:44:02,264
Beom-su is regretting it too.

689
00:44:02,598 --> 00:44:05,225
Let's talk about the rest over a beer.

690
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:07,394
Oh, it's fine.

691
00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:10,606
Okay. Let's eat assorted sashimi
with konowata and dried laver.

692
00:44:10,689 --> 00:44:12,524
Well, I'm fine.

693
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:14,610
Okay, it's across the road. It's close.

694
00:44:33,921 --> 00:44:35,172
This is what I get off work for.

695
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:40,678
So? Will you air Mr. Son's drama?

696
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:42,471
No production company will work on it.

697
00:44:43,597 --> 00:44:45,349
We can take time. It's by a newbie writer.

698
00:44:45,432 --> 00:44:47,059
Will Mr. Son stay still for that?

699
00:44:47,142 --> 00:44:49,061
He should have stayed still.

700
00:44:49,687 --> 00:44:51,313
-What do you mean?
-Nothing.

701
00:44:53,357 --> 00:44:55,776
You know, you're actually helping it.

702
00:44:57,069 --> 00:44:59,279
-Am I?
-Your condition

703
00:44:59,363 --> 00:45:01,657
was to not air Ms. Lim's work.

704
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:04,159
-Yes.
-But Mr. Son is working on it.

705
00:45:04,410 --> 00:45:07,246
The station can't refuse to air it

706
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:09,164
even if they don't like her work now.

707
00:45:09,248 --> 00:45:12,292
They can't make it look like
they are being controlled by you

708
00:45:12,376 --> 00:45:14,837
and ditching the most competent director.

709
00:45:19,216 --> 00:45:20,551
That's right.

710
00:45:22,177 --> 00:45:24,680
I was only joking though. This is fun.

711
00:45:25,180 --> 00:45:26,181
So?

712
00:45:26,849 --> 00:45:29,518
Are you saying Jin-joo's work
isn't worth airing?

713
00:45:29,601 --> 00:45:31,270
No. There's no problem.

714
00:45:32,187 --> 00:45:34,773
They just need some time. That's all.

715
00:45:43,323 --> 00:45:46,201
Staying still like this
at a moment of crisis.

716
00:45:47,077 --> 00:45:48,203
This is my first time.

717
00:45:48,537 --> 00:45:51,165
It kind of makes me feel good.

718
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:52,875
Thank you.

719
00:45:53,208 --> 00:45:56,044
Forget it. I don't even want to
feel proud of myself.

720
00:45:56,128 --> 00:45:58,922
The designer bag
never dropped out of the sky.

721
00:46:01,091 --> 00:46:05,053
I can't believe the only thing
I can get by sitting still is air.

722
00:46:07,764 --> 00:46:09,558
Fine dust.

723
00:46:09,892 --> 00:46:10,893
God...

724
00:46:12,102 --> 00:46:14,688
must be looking at us
as if we're chess pieces.

725
00:46:15,314 --> 00:46:17,065
The pieces on the board

726
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:19,193
are put in a crisis from the moment
they are on.

727
00:46:20,235 --> 00:46:21,487
"Hey, why are you thinking?

728
00:46:21,570 --> 00:46:24,406
You're just pieces that need to run
until you die. Run."

729
00:46:25,574 --> 00:46:29,244
But while I was looking at you,
fighting head-on with God,

730
00:46:29,328 --> 00:46:30,329
I thought,

731
00:46:31,538 --> 00:46:33,749
I should leave you alone.

732
00:46:34,374 --> 00:46:35,250
What?

733
00:46:35,334 --> 00:46:38,795
She's fighting in a realm
that's beyond my reach.

734
00:46:39,087 --> 00:46:41,465
But don't do this too often.

735
00:46:41,632 --> 00:46:42,508
It makes me worried.

736
00:46:43,550 --> 00:46:46,136
-About what?
-If you defeat God, you'll be God.

737
00:46:47,221 --> 00:46:48,805
-But what if you lose?
-I'd die.

738
00:46:48,889 --> 00:46:50,098
That's why I'm worried.

739
00:46:50,849 --> 00:46:54,186
So you want me to finish 16 episodes
before I die?

740
00:46:54,311 --> 00:46:55,354
Is that what you want to say?

741
00:46:55,437 --> 00:46:56,688
I've grown attached to you.

742
00:47:00,484 --> 00:47:01,777
That's it.

743
00:47:14,248 --> 00:47:15,374
Hello!

744
00:47:16,416 --> 00:47:17,834
I'm Son Beom-su.

745
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:26,426
Hello.

746
00:47:26,510 --> 00:47:28,303
Hi.

747
00:47:28,387 --> 00:47:30,597
Let's mooch off them.

748
00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:33,267
-I'm fine.
-Take a seat.

749
00:47:33,809 --> 00:47:34,810
Well.

750
00:47:37,646 --> 00:47:38,772
You know Ms. Jung, right?

751
00:47:38,855 --> 00:47:40,607
Hello, ma'am.

752
00:47:40,691 --> 00:47:42,859
-May we join you?
-Sure.

753
00:47:44,236 --> 00:47:45,487
It's been a while, Mr. Kim.

754
00:47:45,571 --> 00:47:46,613
Hello, Ms. Jung.

755
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:48,699
What? Do you know Hwan-dong?

756
00:47:48,782 --> 00:47:50,951
He was the director of B team
of my drama last year.

757
00:47:51,285 --> 00:47:52,869
Oh, you were the B team director?

758
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:55,622
Director Yang got hurt,
so I filled in for him.

759
00:47:55,706 --> 00:47:57,165
But he worked longer than Director Yang.

760
00:47:57,249 --> 00:48:00,210
-I see. This is great. Order some beers.
-Okay.

761
00:48:01,378 --> 00:48:02,629
Excuse me. Beers, please.

762
00:48:09,428 --> 00:48:11,597
Gosh, eat first.

763
00:48:12,848 --> 00:48:14,016
Him and his dinosaurs.

764
00:48:16,226 --> 00:48:17,936
It's like the age of dinosaurs is back.

765
00:48:19,938 --> 00:48:22,399
I went to watch Jurassic Park once,

766
00:48:22,649 --> 00:48:25,277
and a schoolkid sitting behind me

767
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:27,362
told me all the names of the dinosaurs.

768
00:48:27,946 --> 00:48:29,072
